people.name: Ann  Fedorco
people.notes: Went to USA with father in 1912. Married George Simcoe who was in railroad. George went to saloon a lot. Ann had operation in 1935 and Uncle Johnny provided blood for her as he had the right type. A German doctor stabbed her as she was bloated. She died 3 years later after a visit to Czechoslovakia.

people.name: Joe  Fedorco
people.notes: Used gun to avoid conscription in WWI. Married Suzanne Kudrach from USA who came to visit. He thus became a US citizen and moved to USA in 1938.

people.name: Michael  Fedorco
people.notes: Age 16 went to war. Was POW in Russia. As he spoke German & Russian, a Russian general took him to a dacha with a swimming pool where everyone swam naked. He became connected with the American Consul and in October 1918 he went to USA. Became an electrician for Westinghouse. He made radios and Uncle Johnny made the cabinets in the 1930s when Johnny was in USA.

people.name: John  Fedorco
people.notes: Adopted as indentured servant by the "Grov" when he was 8 years old. Well-educated up to age 17-18. Was scheduled to marry the wealthy Grov's daughter but the Grov died when John was in the army. During 1916 famine he built a water-wheel flour mill and was quite successful. Went to USA and took sister Maryanna who stayed.
